Report: act_report¶

This report describe three insights regarding analyzing WeRateDogs project

  1. Which breed of dog recieved the highest likes and retweets?
  2. Tweet distribution based on the number of favorites and retweets
  3. What is the most used slang (doggo, puppo, pupper, flooper)?

Each insight has its own visualization

1. Which breed of dog recieved the highest likes and retweets?¶

In [1]:
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
%matplotlib inline
In [2]:
master_df = pd.read_csv('twitter_archive_master.csv')

The average retweet and favorite count for each breed was gotten programmatically A barchart is used to show the relationship

In [3]:
master_df.groupby(['breed'])['retweet_count'].mean().plot(kind="bar", figsize=(30,30));
plt.title('Average retweet Per Breed', fontsize=30)
plt.xlabel('Retweet_count', fontsize=25)
plt.ylabel('Breed', fontsize=25)
plt.show()
  • The graph shows the average retweet count with regards to Breed
  • From the graph it shows English springler has the highest likes
In [4]:
master_df.groupby(['breed'])['favorite_count'].mean().plot(kind="bar", figsize=(30,30));
plt.title('Average favourite_count Per Breed', fontsize=30)
plt.xlabel('Favorite_count', fontsize=25)
plt.ylabel('Breed', fontsize=25)
plt.show()

The graph shows the average favourite count with regards to Breed From the graph it shows English springler has the highest likes

2. Twitter distribution based on the number of favorites and retweets¶

To show the relationship between favourite and retweet a scatter plot was used

In [5]:
# x-axis
plt.xlabel('retweet')
# y-axis
plt.ylabel('favorite')
# Title of the histogram
plt.title('Relationship between retweet and favorite')
plt.scatter(master_df['retweet_count'], master_df['favorite_count'])
plt.show()
  • There is a positive correlation between retweet and favorite
  • The higher the retweet the higher the favorite

3. What is the most used slang (doggo, puppo, pupper, flooper)?¶

The count of slang is shown below:

In [6]:
slage_count = pd.Series(master_df['slang']).value_counts(ascending = False)
slage_count
Out[6]:
none       1200
pupper      121
doggo        42
puppo        16
floofer       5
Name: slang, dtype: int64
In [7]:
diagram = slage_count.plot.barh(fontsize = 8)
diagram.set(title = 'Slang Count')
diagram.set_xlabel('Count')
diagram.set_ylabel('slang')
plt.show()

Most dogs do not have either of the 4 slangs, for the dogs with slangs pupper has the highest count

df_breed = master_df.groupby(['slang'],as_index=False)['favorite_count'].mean()
